@@eThe Saltglass Reach@@N

The Saltglass Reach is the jurisdictional transition corridor between
the inland desert and the eastern sea. It is not empty transit space
but a @@ylegal gradient@@N where charter law gives way to maritime risk
law across four distinct bands of terrain.

The @@WMirror Flats@@N are hard salt crust -- the terminal evaporation
basin of the vanished Iseth Reach river. They blind by day and
reflect moonlight at night. Caravans cross at dawn and dusk when the
reflection angle is survivable. The @@rGlasswind Belts@@N are fields of
wind-cut silica shards formed when the Ninth Meridian's thermal pulse
fused surface sand into brittle glass. Experienced guides read glass
color to navigate: milky shards mean stable ground, amber warns of
thermal fault proximity, @@dviolet signals eclipse-rite residue@@N.

The @@yTariff Cairn Lines@@N are ruined checkpoint chains where cargo
once transitioned from inland water-law to maritime levy law. Three
parallel routes served different needs: the Swift Line for light
high-value cargo, the Heavy Road for bulk commodities, and the
Sealed Route for funerary and relic consignments under armed escort.

At the coast, the @@eTidemouth Dunes@@N mark the approach to the port
city of Mafdet. The boundary stone called the @@WShoreward Seal@@N once
served as the legal threshold between jurisdictions.

The defining institution was the @@yShoreward Conversion@@N: the formal
process by which cargo, contracts, and obligations were translated
from inland desert law to maritime law. Water-debt was discharged by
pouring a measured volume onto the basalt slab. Cargo owners spoke a
formulaic oath transferring liability from road to sea. Specialist
@@WShoreward Assessors@@N bridged both legal traditions through the
Shoreward Tables -- conversion charts whose descendants became
Mafdet's modern Saltweight standard.

@@gReach Wardens@@N patrol the surviving cairn lines and issue transit
seals accepted with varying trust at both ends. @@rRed Sand Outriders@@N
from Mafdet's debt-leverage consortium prey on distressed caravans.
@@dGlasswalk Guides@@N -- hereditary desert navigators with chitin-soled
shoes -- remain strictly neutral, guiding anyone who pays. @@rSynod
Whisper Cells@@N use the Glasswind Belts as smuggling corridors.

The Reach is not a natural landscape. The salt is the dead river's
mineral deposit. The glass is the catastrophe's echo. The cairns are
a collapsed legal order. Every surface carries the fingerprint of
institutions that tried to govern the ungovernable crossing from
land to sea.
